ChatGPT said:

Ye error:

sql
Each child in a list should have a unique "key" prop.

ka matlab hai: React me jab aap list render karte ho (e.g. via .map()), to har child element ko ek unique key prop dena zaroori hota hai.

🔍 Example of Problematic Code (likely in your HomePage):

tsx
{data.map((item) => (
  <div>{item.title}</div> // ❌ No "key" prop
))}

Yahan har <div> me key prop missing hai, isliye React warning de raha hai.

✅ Correct Way (Fix):

Aapko har element ko unique key deni hogi:

tsx
{data.map((item) => (
  <div key={item.id}>{item.title}</div> // ✅ key added
))}

🔑 Notes:

  • Agar aapke item me id ya uuid jaisa kuch unique hai, use use karo.

  • Agar id nahi hai, to temporary workaround ke liye index bhi use kar sakte ho (not ideal for dynamic lists):

tsx
{data.map((item, index) => (
  <div key={index}>{item.title}</div> // 😬 Fallback (not best practice)
))}

🔗 React Official Link:

React ka message aapko ye link de raha hai:
https://react.dev/link/warning-keys
Yeh explain karta hai ki key ka use React ko efficiently diff karne me madad karta hai (DOM performance ke liye).

📌 Summary:

  • List render karte waqt .map() ke andar har child ko unique key prop dena hota hai.

  • Best option: key={item.id} ya koi aur unique identifier.

  • Temporary: key={index} (agar kuch aur nahi ho to).

Agar aap HomePage ka exact .map() block bhej doge to mai direct fix bhi de sakta hoon.

✅ Here's how to fix it:

You have this problematic code:

tsx
{quickLinks.map((link) => (
  <div className={`rounded-xl p-4 text-center text-white ${link.bg}`}>
    <Link href={link.href} key={link.name}>
      <div className="cursor-pointer">
        <Image
          src={link.image}
          alt={link.name}
          width={100}

      </div>
    </Link>
    <p className="text-2xl font-semibold">{link.name}</p>
    <p className="text-sm">{link.description}</p>
  </div>
))}

Here, key={link.name} is on <Link>, but it should be on the outermost element returned inside .map() — i.e., the <div>.

    key={link.name}

    <Link href={link.href}>

ChatGPT said:

The error:

javascript
Failed to parse feedback params: URIError: URI malformed
    at decodeURIComponent

...means that decodeURIComponent() is trying to decode a string that is not a valid URI-encoded format. This usually happens when:

  • A query parameter or URL segment contains invalid characters, e.g., % not followed by two hexadecimal digits.

  • You call decodeURIComponent() on something that hasn't been encoded.

  • A malformed or broken string is being passed from the URL.

🔍 Here's what might be causing it in your file:

Looking at this part of the stack trace:

less
Score.useEffect (C:\Users\rinki\OneDrive\Desktop\Elite_CV\eliteCV\src\app\score\page.tsx:51:35)

You likely have a line like this in your page.tsx around line 51:

ts
const feedback = decodeURIComponent(params.get("feedback") ?? "");

or something similar.

✅ How to fix it:

  1. Wrap decodeURIComponent() in a try/catch block to prevent app crash:

ts
let feedback = "";
try {
  feedback = decodeURIComponent(params.get("feedback") ?? "");
} catch (err) {
  console.error("Failed to decode feedback param", err);
  feedback = ""; // Or some default fallback
}

  1. Validate input before decoding. Make sure params.get("feedback") is not malformed.

  2. Check where the URL param is coming from — maybe it's incorrectly set. For example:

    • ?feedback=abc% ← ❌ this is broken (incomplete %)

    • Use encodeURIComponent() when setting feedback parameters to avoid breaking URLs.

✅ Example Fix for a full useEffect

tsx
useEffect(() => {
  const params = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);
  try {
    const feedbackRaw = params.get("feedback");
    const feedback = feedbackRaw ? decodeURIComponent(feedbackRaw) : "";
    setFeedback(feedback); // your state logic
  } catch (error) {
    console.error("Failed to parse feedback params:", error);
  }
}, []);

💡 Tip:

If you control the redirect or link that includes ?feedback=..., make sure it's properly encoded using:

js
const url = `/score?feedback=${encodeURIComponent("some string with % or & or spaces")}`;

tsx
"use client";

import { useEffect, useState } from "react";
import { useSearchParams } from "next/navigation";
import { useSession } from "next-auth/react";
import { AlertTriangle } from "lucide-react";

const API_BASE_URL = "https://your-api-base-url.com"; // 🔁 Update this
const RESUME_SCORES = `${API_BASE_URL}/resume/scores`;

export default function Score() {
  const { data: session, status } = useSession();
  const searchParams = useSearchParams();

  const [theme, setTheme] = useState<"light" | "dark">("light");
  const [score, setScore] = useState<number | null>(null);
  const [feedback, setFeedback] = useState<string | null>(null);
  const [strengths, setStrengths] = useState<string[]>([]);
  const [weaknesses, setWeaknesses] = useState<string[]>([]);
  const [suggestions, setSuggestions] = useState<string[]>([]);
  const [previewURL, setPreviewURL] = useState<string | null>(null);

  useEffect(() => {
    const savedTheme = localStorage.getItem("theme");
    if (savedTheme === "dark") setTheme("dark");
  }, []);

  useEffect(() => {
    localStorage.setItem("theme", theme);
  }, [theme]);

  const toggleTheme = () => {
    setTheme((prev) => (prev === "light" ? "dark" : "light"));
  };

  // ✅ Fetch preview from sessionStorage & get score from API
  useEffect(() => {
    const preview = sessionStorage.getItem("resumePreviewURL");
    if (preview) {
      setPreviewURL(preview);

      // ✅ Call the resume scoring API
      const fetchScore = async () => {
        try {
          const response = await fetch(RESUME_SCORES, {
            method: "POST",
            headers: {
              "Content-Type": "application/json",
            },
            body: JSON.stringify({ resumeURL: preview }),
          });

          if (!response.ok) throw new Error("Failed to fetch score");

          const data = await response.json();

          setScore(data.score || 0);
          setFeedback(data.feedback || "");
          setStrengths(data.strengths || []);
          setWeaknesses(data.weaknesses || []);
          setSuggestions(data.suggestions || []);
        } catch (error) {
          console.error("❌ Error fetching resume score:", error);
        }
      };

      fetchScore();
    }
  }, []);

  // ✅ Optional: handle URL params safely
  useEffect(() => {
    try {
      const feedbackParam = searchParams.get("feedback");
      if (feedbackParam) setFeedback(decodeURIComponent(feedbackParam));
    } catch (error) {
      console.warn("⚠️ Invalid feedback param", error);
    }
  }, [searchParams]);

  const progressColor = (score: number | null) => {
    if (score === null) return "stroke-gray-300";
    if (score >= 85) return "stroke-green-500";
    if (score >= 70) return "stroke-yellow-400";
    return "stroke-red-500";
  };

  const circularProgress = (
    <svg width="80" height="80">
      <circle cx="40" cy="40" r="35" stroke="#E5E7EB" strokeWidth="8" fill="none" />
      <circle
        cx="40"
        cy="40"
        r="35"
        strokeLinecap="round"
        strokeWidth="8"
        fill="none"
        className={progressColor(score)}
        strokeDasharray={220}
        strokeDashoffset={score !== null ? 220 - (220 * score) / 100 : 220}
      />
      <text
        x="50%"
        y="50%"
        textAnchor="middle"
        dy=".3em"
        className={`text-xl font-bold ${theme === "dark" ? "fill-white" : "fill-gray-800"}`}
      >
        {score ?? "--"}
      </text>
    </svg>
  );

  return (
    <div
      className={`min-h-screen flex font-sans ${
        theme === "dark" ? "bg-black text-white" : "text-black"
      }`}
      style={
        theme === "light"
          ? {
              backgroundImage:
                "radial-gradient(at 50% 100%, rgb(156, 103, 213), rgb(220, 151, 165))",
            }
          : {}
      }
    >
      {/* Toggle Button */}
      <button
        onClick={toggleTheme}
        className="fixed top-4 right-4 z-50 px-4 py-2 bg-gray-800 text-white rounded shadow hover:bg-gray-700 text-sm"
      >
        Toggle {theme === "light" ? "Dark" : "Light"} Mode
      </button>

      {/* Sidebar */}
      <div className="w-64 p-6 border-r flex flex-col justify-between">
        <div>
          <div className="flex justify-center mb-6">{circularProgress}</div>
          <div className="text-center text-sm text-green-500 mb-4">OVERALL SCORE</div>

          <div className="space-y-4">
            <div>
              <h3 className="text-sm text-green-500 mb-1">STRENGTHS</h3>
              <ul className="text-sm space-y-1">
                {strengths.map((item, i) => (
                  <li key={i} className="flex justify-between">
                    <span>{item}</span>
                    <span className="text-green-500 font-bold">✓</span>
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 className="text-sm font-semibold text-red-400 mb-1">WEAKNESSES</h3>
              <ul className="text-sm space-y-1">
                {weaknesses.map((item, i) => (
                  <li key={i} className="flex justify-between">
                    <span>{item}</span>
                    <span className="text-yellow-400 font-bold">⚠</span>
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <button className="bg-blue-600 text-white py-2 rounded mt-6 text-sm font-semibold shadow hover:bg-blue-700">
          Unlock full report
        </button>
      </div>

      {/* Main Content */}
      <div className="flex-1 p-8 space-y-6">
        <h1 className="text-xl font-bold text-green-600">
          {status === "loading"
            ? "Loading..."
            : `Hi, ${session?.user?.name || session?.user?.email || "User"}`}
        </h1>

        <div
          className={`p-6 rounded shadow space-y-4 ${
            theme === "dark" ? "bg-gray-900 text-white" : "bg-white"
          }`}
        >
          <h2 className="text-lg font-bold">
            Your resume scored {score !== null ? `${score} out of 100` : "is loading..."}
          </h2>

          {feedback && (
            <p
              className={`text-sm italic border-l-4 pl-4 ${
                theme === "dark"
                  ? "text-yellow-200 border-yellow-600"
                  : "text-gray-700 border-yellow-400"
              }`}
            >
              {feedback}
            </p>
          )}

          <div className="w-full h-4 bg-gradient-to-r from-red-400 via-yellow-300 to-green-400 rounded mt-3 relative">
            <div
              className="absolute top-0 h-4 bg-purple-600 rounded"
              style={{ width: `${score ?? 0}%` }}
            ></div>
          </div>

          <div className="mt-4">
            <h3 className="text-sm font-semibold">Suggestions</h3>
            <ul className="text-sm mt-2 space-y-1">
              {suggestions.map((item, i) => (
                <li
                  key={i}
                  className={`list-disc list-inside ${
                    theme === "dark" ? "text-gray-300" : "text-gray-700"
                  }`}
                >
                  {item}
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div
            className={`flex items-start border rounded p-3 mt-4 text-sm ${
              theme === "dark"
                ? "bg-yellow-950 border-yellow-600 text-yellow-300"
                : "bg-yellow-50 border-yellow-300 text-yellow-800"
            }`}
          >
            <AlertTriangle size={16} className="mr-2 mt-0.5" />
            Use this feedback to revise your resume and try again.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* Preview */}
      <div className="w-[600px] border-l p-4 overflow-auto">
        <h2 className="text-sm font-semibold mb-2">Resume Preview</h2>
        {previewURL ? (
          <iframe
            src={previewURL}
            className="w-full h-[90vh] border"
            title="Resume Preview"
          />
        ) : (
          <p className="text-sm italic text-gray-400">No resume uploaded.</p>
        )}
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}

To meet your exact requirement — keep the UI same, upload the resume, show uploading process, and then redirect to /score page where feedback, strengths, etc. are handled and shown — we’ll refactor the UploadResume component slightly:

We'll remove all feedback handling logic from UploadResume and just handle upload + redirect with the file preview stored.

Here is your updated full code for UploadResume.tsx:

tsx
"use client";

import React, { useState, useEffect } from "react";
import { CloudArrowUpIcon, LockClosedIcon } from "@heroicons/react/24/outline";
import { useRouter } from "next/navigation";
import { useSession } from "next-auth/react";
import Header from "../pages/components/Header";
import Lottie from "lottie-react";
import uploadingAnimation from "@/app/animations/loader.json";
import { verifyEmailWithServer } from "@/app/utils/auth";

export default function UploadResume() {
  const [selectedFile, setSelectedFile] = useState<File | null>(null);
  const [isUploading, setIsUploading] = useState(false);
  const [message, setMessage] = useState<string | null>(null);

  const { data: session, status } = useSession();
  const router = useRouter();

  useEffect(() => {
    if (status === "unauthenticated") {
      router.push("/login");
    }
  }, [status, router]);

  if (status === "loading") {
    return <div className="text-center py-10 text-xl">Loading...</div>;
  }

  const uploadResume = async (file: File, token: string) => {
    const formData = new FormData();
    formData.append("file", file);

    const response = await fetch(
      "https://ai-cv-builder-be.fly.dev/resume/upload",
      {
        method: "POST",
        headers: {
          Authorization: `Bearer ${token}`,
        },
        body: formData,
      }
    );

    const result = await response.json();

    if (!response.ok || result.is_resume === false) {
      throw new Error("Invalid resume or upload failed");
    }

    return result;
  };

  const handleFileChange = async (e: React.ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>) => {
    const file = e.target.files?.[0];

    if (
      file &&
      (file.type === "application/pdf" ||
        file.type ===
          "application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document")
    ) {
      setSelectedFile(file);
      setIsUploading(true);
      setMessage("Processing your resume...");

      try {
        let token = localStorage.getItem("access_token");

        if (!token && session?.user?.email) {
          const [firstName = "", lastName = ""] =
            session.user.name?.split(" ") || [];
          const result = await verifyEmailWithServer({
            email: session.user.email,
            first_name: firstName,
            last_name: lastName,
            phone: "0000000000",
          });

          token = result.access_token;
          localStorage.setItem("access_token", token);
        }

        if (!token) throw new Error("Access token missing.");

        const result = await uploadResume(file, token);

        // Save preview URL for iframe display
        const previewURL = URL.createObjectURL(file);
        sessionStorage.setItem("resumePreviewURL", previewURL);

        // Just redirect to score page — score.tsx will handle all UI rendering
        router.push("/score");
      } catch (error: any) {
        console.error("🚨 Upload error:", error);
        setIsUploading(false);
        setMessage("❌ Upload failed. " + error.message);
      }
    } else {
      setMessage("❗ Please upload a valid PDF or DOCX file.");
    }
  };

  if (isUploading) {
    return (
      <div
        className="min-h-screen flex flex-col items-center justify-center"
        style={{
          backgroundImage:
            "radial-gradient(at 50% 100%,rgb(115, 198, 155),rgb(57, 153, 104))",
        }}
      >
        <div className="w-64 h-64">
          <Lottie animationData={uploadingAnimation} loop={true} />
        </div>
        <p className="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-700 mt-4">
          Uploading and analyzing your resume...
        </p>
      </div>
    );
  }

  return (
    <>
      <Header />
      <div
        className="min-h-screen flex flex-col items-center justify-center px-4 text-white text-center"
        style={{
          backgroundImage:
            "radial-gradient(at 50% 100%,rgb(115, 198, 155),rgb(57, 153, 104))",
        }}
      >
        <h1 className="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Upload Your Resume</h1>
        <p className="mb-6">
          Career Level: <span className="font-semibold">Senior-level</span>{" "}
          <span className="underline cursor-pointer text-blue-300">
            (Change)
          </span>
        </p>

        <label
          htmlFor="resumeUpload"
          className="w-full max-w-lg border-2 border-dashed border-white/50 p-12 rounded-lg mb-6 cursor-pointer hover:bg-white/10 transition"
        >
          <CloudArrowUpIcon className="w-16 h-16 mx-auto text-white/70 mb-4" />
          <p className="text-white/80">
            Click to browse or drop your resume here.
          </p>

You’re trying to POST the resumeURL (which is just a local preview URL like blob:http://...) to the RESUME_SCORES API, which expects an actual uploaded resume on the backend to analyze — not a local preview.

🔧 Step 1: Update useEffect to fetch from API using token

Replace your fetchScore logic with this:

tsx
useEffect(() => {
  const preview = sessionStorage.getItem("resumePreviewURL");
  if (preview) setPreviewURL(preview);

  const fetchScore = async () => {
    try {
      const token = localStorage.getItem("access_token");
      if (!token) throw new Error("Missing access token.");

      const response = await fetch(API_ROUTES.RESUME_SCORES, {
        method: "GET",
        headers: {
          Authorization: `Bearer ${token}`,
          "Content-Type": "application/json",
        },
      });

      if (!response.ok) throw new Error("Failed to fetch score");

      const data = await response.json();

      setScore(data.score ?? 0);
      setFeedback(data.feedback ?? "");
      setStrengths(data.strengths ?? []);
      setWeaknesses(data.weaknesses ?? []);
      setSuggestions(data.suggestions ?? []);
    } catch (error) {
      console.error("❌ Error fetching resume score:", error);
    }
  };

  fetchScore();
}, []);

🔥 Important: this assumes your API GET /resume/scores returns a response like:

✅ UploadResume.tsx

This version:

  • Uploads the resume

  • Gets the access token

  • Stores the uploaded file’s preview URL

  • Redirects to /score (now we don’t pass score data in URL)

tsx
"use client";

import React, { useState, useEffect } from "react";
import { CloudArrowUpIcon, LockClosedIcon } from "@heroicons/react/24/outline";
import { useRouter } from "next/navigation";
import { useSession } from "next-auth/react";
import Header from "../pages/components/Header";
import Lottie from "lottie-react";
import uploadingAnimation from "@/app/animations/loader.json";
import { verifyEmailWithServer } from "@/app/utils/auth";

export default function UploadResume() {
  const [selectedFile, setSelectedFile] = useState<File | null>(null);
  const [isUploading, setIsUploading] = useState(false);
  const [message, setMessage] = useState<string | null>(null);

  const { data: session, status } = useSession();
  const router = useRouter();

  useEffect(() => {
    if (status === "unauthenticated") {
      router.push("/login");
    }
  }, [status, router]);

  if (status === "loading") {
    return <div className="text-center py-10 text-xl">Loading...</div>;
  }

  const uploadResume = async (file: File, token: string) => {
    const formData = new FormData();
    formData.append("file", file);

    const response = await fetch(
      "https://ai-cv-builder-be.fly.dev/resume/upload",
      {
        method: "POST",
        headers: {
          Authorization: `Bearer ${token}`,
        },
        body: formData,
      }
    );

    const result = await response.json();

    if (!response.ok || result.is_resume === false) {
      throw new Error("Invalid resume or upload failed");
    }

    return result;
  };

  const handleFileChange = async (e: React.ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>) => {
    const file = e.target.files?.[0];

    if (
      file &&
      (file.type === "application/pdf" ||
        file.type ===
          "application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document")
    ) {
      setSelectedFile(file);
      setIsUploading(true);
      setMessage("Processing your resume...");

      try {
        let token = localStorage.getItem("access_token");

        if (!token && session?.user?.email) {
          const [firstName = "", lastName = ""] =
            session.user.name?.split(" ") || [];
          const result = await verifyEmailWithServer({
            email: session.user.email,
            first_name: firstName,
            last_name: lastName,
            phone: "0000000000",
          });

          token = result.access_token;
          localStorage.setItem("access_token", token);
        }

        if (!token) throw new Error("Access token missing.");

        await uploadResume(file, token); // ✅ Upload only, don't need to get score here

        const previewURL = URL.createObjectURL(file);
        sessionStorage.setItem("resumePreviewURL", previewURL);

        router.push("/score");
      } catch (error: any) {
        console.error("🚨 Upload error:", error);
        setIsUploading(false);
        setMessage("❌ Upload failed. " + error.message);
      }
    } else {
      setMessage("❗ Please upload a valid PDF or DOCX file.");
    }
  };

  if (isUploading) {
    return (
      <div
        className="min-h-screen flex flex-col items-center justify-center"
        style={{
          backgroundImage:
            "radial-gradient(at 50% 100%,rgb(115, 198, 155),rgb(57, 153, 104))",
        }}
      >
        <div className="w-64 h-64">
          <Lottie animationData={uploadingAnimation} loop={true} />
        </div>
        <p className="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-700 mt-4">
          Uploading and analyzing your resume...
        </p>
      </div>
    );
  }

  return (
    <>
      <Header />
      <div
        className="min-h-screen flex flex-col items-center justify-center px-4 text-white text-center"
        style={{
          backgroundImage:
            "radial-gradient(at 50% 100%,rgb(115, 198, 155),rgb(57, 153, 104))",
        }}
      >
        <h1 className="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Upload Your Resume</h1>
        <p className="mb-6">
          Career Level: <span className="font-semibold">Senior-level</span>{" "}
          <span className="underline cursor-pointer text-blue-300">
            (Change)
          </span>
        </p>

        <label
          htmlFor="resumeUpload"
          className="w-full max-w-lg border-2 border-dashed border-white/50 p-12 rounded-lg mb-6 cursor-pointer hover:bg-white/10 transition"
        >
          <CloudArrowUpIcon className="w-16 h-16 mx-auto text-white/70 mb-4" />
          <p className="text-white/80">
            Click to browse or drop your resume here.
          </p>
          <p className="mt-2 text-sm text-white/90">
            English resumes in <span className="font-bold">PDF</span> or{" "}
            <span className="font-bold">DOCX</span> only. Max 2MB file size.
          </p>
          <input
            type="file"
            id="resumeUpload"
            accept=".pdf,.docx"
            onChange={handleFileChange}
            className="hidden"
          />
        </label>

        {selectedFile && (
          <p className="text-green-800 mb-2">
            Selected file:{" "}
            <span className="font-semibold">{selectedFile.name}</span>
          </p>
        )}

        {message && (
          <p className="mt-4 px-4 py-2 rounded-md bg-white/20 text-sm">
            {message}
          </p>
        )}

        <div className="flex items-center text-xs text-white/60 mt-4">
          <LockClosedIcon className="w-4 h-4 mr-2" />
          <span>
            We're committed to your{" "}
            <span className="underline cursor-pointer">privacy</span>. Your
            resume is processed securely on our servers and is private to you.
          </span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </>
  );
}

✅ Score.tsx

This version:

  • Gets the access token from localStorage

  • Calls the GET /resume/scores API to fetch analysis data

  • Displays score, strengths, weaknesses, suggestions, and preview

tsx
"use client";

import { useEffect, useState } from "react";
import { useSession } from "next-auth/react";
import { AlertTriangle } from "lucide-react";
import { API_ROUTES } from "@/app/lib/config"; // Make sure this contains RESUME_SCORES

export default function Score() {
  const { data: session, status } = useSession();

  const [theme, setTheme] = useState<"light" | "dark">("light");
  const [score, setScore] = useState<number | null>(null);
  const [feedback, setFeedback] = useState<string | null>(null);
  const [strengths, setStrengths] = useState<string[]>([]);
  const [weaknesses, setWeaknesses] = useState<string[]>([]);
  const [suggestions, setSuggestions] = useState<string[]>([]);
  const [previewURL, setPreviewURL] = useState<string | null>(null);

  useEffect(() => {
    const savedTheme = localStorage.getItem("theme");
    if (savedTheme === "dark") setTheme("dark");
  }, []);

  useEffect(() => {
    localStorage.setItem("theme", theme);
  }, [theme]);

  const toggleTheme = () => {
    setTheme((prev) => (prev === "light" ? "dark" : "light"));
  };

  useEffect(() => {
    const preview = sessionStorage.getItem("resumePreviewURL");
    if (preview) setPreviewURL(preview);

    const fetchScore = async () => {
      try {
        const token = localStorage.getItem("access_token");
        if (!token) throw new Error("Missing access token.");

        const response = await fetch(API_ROUTES.RESUME_SCORES, {
          method: "GET",
          headers: {
            Authorization: `Bearer ${token}`,
            "Content-Type": "application/json",
          },
        });

        if (!response.ok) throw new Error("Failed to fetch score");

        const data = await response.json();

        setScore(data.score ?? 0);
        setFeedback(data.feedback ?? "");
        setStrengths(data.strengths ?? []);
        setWeaknesses(data.weaknesses ?? []);
        setSuggestions(data.suggestions ?? []);
      } catch (error) {
        console.error("❌ Error fetching resume score:", error);
      }
    };

    fetchScore();
  }, []);

  const progressColor = (score: number | null) => {
    if (score === null) return "stroke-gray-300";
    if (score >= 85) return "stroke-green-500";
    if (score >= 70) return "stroke-yellow-400";
    return "stroke-red-500";
  };

  const circularProgress = (
    <svg width="80" height="80">
      <circle cx="40" cy="40" r="35" stroke="#E5E7EB" strokeWidth="8" fill="none" />
      <circle
        cx="40"
        cy="40"
        r="35"
        strokeLinecap="round"
        strokeWidth="8"
        fill="none"
        className={progressColor(score)}
        strokeDasharray={220}
        strokeDashoffset={score !== null ? 220 - (220 * score) / 100 : 220}
      />
      <text
        x="50%"
        y="50%"
        textAnchor="middle"
        dy=".3em"
        className={`text-xl font-bold ${theme === "dark" ? "fill-white" : "fill-gray-800"}`}
      >
        {score ?? "--"}
      </text>
    </svg>
  );

  return (
    <div
      className={`min-h-screen flex font-sans ${
        theme === "dark" ? "bg-black text-white" : "text-black"
      }`}
      style={
        theme === "light"
          ? {
              backgroundImage:
                "radial-gradient(at 50% 100%, rgb(156, 103, 213), rgb(220, 151, 165))",
            }
          : {}
      }
    >
      {/* Theme Toggle */}
      <button
        onClick={toggleTheme}
        className="fixed top-4 right-4 z-50 px-4 py-2 bg-gray-800 text-white rounded shadow hover:bg-gray-700 text-sm"
      >
        Toggle {theme === "light" ? "Dark" : "Light"} Mode
      </button>

      {/* Sidebar */}
      <div className="w-64 p-6 border-r flex flex-col justify-between">
        <div>
          <div className="flex justify-center mb-6">{circularProgress}</div>
          <div className="text-center text-sm text-green-500 mb-4">OVERALL SCORE</div>

          <div className="space-y-4">
            <div>
              <h3 className="text-sm text-green-500 mb-1">STRENGTHS</h3>
              <ul className="text-sm space-y-1">
                {strengths.map((item, i) => (
                  <li key={i} className="flex justify-between">
                    <span>{item}</span>
                    <span className="text-green-500 font-bold">✓</span>
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 className="text-sm font-semibold text-red-400 mb-1">WEAKNESSES</h3>
              <ul className="text-sm space-y-1">
                {weaknesses.map((item, i) => (
                  <li key={i} className="flex justify-between">
                    <span>{item}</span>
                    <span className="text-yellow-400 font-bold">⚠</span>
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <button className="bg-blue-600 text-white py-2 rounded mt-6 text-sm font-semibold shadow hover:bg-blue-700">
          Unlock full report
        </button>
      </div>

      {/* Main */}
      <div className="flex-1 p-8 space-y-6">
        <h1 className="text-xl font-bold text-green-600">
          {status === "loading"
            ? "Loading..."
            : `Hi, ${session?.user?.name || session?.user?.email || "User"}`}
        </h1>

        <div
          className={`p-6 rounded shadow space-y-4 ${
            theme === "dark" ? "bg-gray-900 text-white" : "bg-white"
          }`}
        >
          <h2 className="text-lg font-bold">
            Your resume scored {score !== null ? `${score} out of 100` : "is loading..."}
          </h2>

          {feedback && (
            <p
              className={`text-sm italic border-l-4 pl-4 ${
                theme === "dark"
                  ? "text-yellow-200 border-yellow-600"
                  : "text-gray-700 border-yellow-400"
              }`}
            >
              {feedback}
            </p>
          )}

          <div className="w-full h-4 bg-gradient-to-r from-red-400 via-yellow-300 to-green-400 rounded mt-3 relative">
            <div
              className="absolute top-0 h-4 bg-purple-600 rounded"
              style={{ width: `${score ?? 0}%` }}
            ></div>
          </div>

          <div className="mt-4">
            <h3 className="text-sm font-semibold">Suggestions</h3>
            <ul className="text-sm mt-2 space-y-1">
              {suggestions.map((item, i) => (
                <li
                  key={i}
                  className={`list-disc list-inside ${
                    theme === "dark" ? "text-gray-300" : "text-gray-700"
                  }`}
                >
                  {item}
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div
            className={`flex items-start border rounded p-3 mt-4 text-sm ${
              theme === "dark"
                ? "bg-yellow-950 border-yellow-600 text-yellow-300"
                : "bg-yellow-50 border-yellow-300 text-yellow-800"
            }`}
          >
            <AlertTriangle size={16} className="mr-2 mt-0.5" />
            Use this feedback to revise your resume and try again.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* Preview */}
      <div className="w-[600px] border-l p-4 overflow-auto">
        <h2 className="text-sm font-semibold mb-2">Resume Preview</h2>
        {previewURL ? (
          <iframe
            src={previewURL}
            className="w-full h-[90vh] border"
            title="Resume Preview"
          />
        ) : (
          <p className="text-sm italic text-gray-400">No resume uploaded.</p>
        )}
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}

🧾 2. Frontend: UploadResume.tsx

This component uploads your resume, saves the JWT, stores a preview URL, and navigates to /score.

tsx
"use client";
import React, { useState, useEffect } from "react";
import { CloudArrowUpIcon, LockClosedIcon } from "@heroicons/react/24/outline";
import { useRouter } from "next/navigation";
import { useSession } from "next-auth/react";
import Header from "../pages/components/Header";
import Lottie from "lottie-react";
import uploadingAnimation from "@/app/animations/loader.json";
import { verifyEmailWithServer } from "@/app/utils/auth";

export default function UploadResume() {
  const [selectedFile, setSelectedFile] = useState<File | null>(null);
  const [isUploading, setIsUploading] = useState(false);
  const [message, setMessage] = useState<string | null>(null);
  const { data: session, status } = useSession();
  const router = useRouter();

  useEffect(() => {
    if (status === "unauthenticated") router.push("/login");
  }, [status, router]);

  if (status === "loading") return <div>Loading...</div>;

  const uploadResume = async (file: File, token: string) => {
    const formData = new FormData();
    formData.append("file", file);
    const res = await fetch("https://ai-cv-builder-be.fly.dev/resume/upload", {
      method: "POST",
      headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` },
      body: formData,
    });
    const data = await res.json();
    if (!res.ok || data.is_resume !== true) throw new Error("Upload failed");
    return data;
  };

  const handleFileChange = async (e: React.ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>) => {
    const file = e.target.files?.[0];
    if (!file) return;
    if (!["application/pdf", "application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document"].includes(file.type)) {
      return setMessage("Please upload a valid PDF or DOCX");
    }
    setSelectedFile(file);
    setIsUploading(true);
    setMessage("Uploading...");
    try {
      let token = localStorage.getItem("access_token");
      if (!token && session?.user?.email) {
        const [fn, ln] = session.user.name?.split(" ") || ["", ""];
        const result = await verifyEmailWithServer({ email: session.user.email, first_name: fn, last_name: ln, phone: "0000000000" });
        token = result.access_token;
        localStorage.setItem("access_token", token);
      }
      if (!token) throw new Error("Access token missing");
      await uploadResume(file, token);
      const previewURL = URL.createObjectURL(file);
      sessionStorage.setItem("resumePreviewURL", previewURL);
      router.push("/score");
    } catch (err: any) {
      console.error(err);
      setIsUploading(false);
      setMessage("Upload failed: " + err.message);
    }
  };

  if (isUploading) {
    return (
      <div className="min-h-screen flex flex-col items-center justify-center">
        <Lottie animationData={uploadingAnimation} />
        <p>{message}</p>
      </div>
    );
  }

  return (
    <>
      <Header />
      <div className="min-h-screen flex flex-col items-center justify-center px-4 text-white">
        <h1 className="text-3xl">Upload Your Resume</h1>
        <label className="border-dashed border-2 p-12 cursor-pointer">
          <CloudArrowUpIcon className="w-16 h-16 mx-auto" />
          <p>PDF or DOCX only, max 2MB</p>
          <input type="file" accept=".pdf,.docx" onChange={handleFileChange} hidden />
        </label>
        {message && <p>{message}</p>}
        <div className="flex items-center text-xs text-white/60">
          <LockClosedIcon className="w-4 h-4 mr-2" />
          <span>Your resume is processed securely.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </>
  );
}

ChatGPT said:

The error you're seeing:

javascript
❌ Failed to parse feedback params: URIError: URI malformed
    at decodeURIComponent (<anonymous>)

means your code (or the backend) is trying to decodeURIComponent() a string that is not properly URL-encoded — maybe it contains invalid characters (like % not followed by hex digits, or garbage input).

✅ Common Causes

  1. Double Encoding / Decoding
    You might be decoding an already-decoded string.

  2. Corrupted Token or URL Param
    If you’re passing a token or query param in the URL (e.g. ?feedback=...) and it's not correctly encoded, decodeURIComponent() will fail.

    Example of bad input:

    perl
    ?feedback=Great%resume%20but%20needs%20%improvement
                       ↑ invalid %i

  3. Incorrect use of decodeURIComponent()
    Using it on the entire URL or on something that isn’t a URL-encoded value.

🔍 How to Fix

✅ Step 1: Check where decodeURIComponent() is used

  • Frontend: Search your codebase for decodeURIComponent( — are you decoding something that wasn’t encoded?

  • Backend: Same thing — maybe you're decoding request params without first checking if they’re URI-encoded.

✅ Step 2: Use encodeURIComponent() correctly when sending

Wherever you send data into the URL (like:

js
const feedback = "Great resume, but needs improvement!";
const safeParam = encodeURIComponent(feedback);

...then decode it later:

js
const decoded = decodeURIComponent(safeParam);

🔧 Example Fix

ts
// BAD: decoding a raw string
decodeURIComponent("Great%resume") // ❌ will throw URIError

// GOOD
const safe = encodeURIComponent("Great resume!");
decodeURIComponent(safe); // ✅ fine

🔎 Debug Suggestion

Add a try/catch to see what’s being decoded:

ts
try {
  const decoded = decodeURIComponent(feedbackParam);
} catch (e) {
  console.error("❌ Failed to decode:", feedbackParam);
}

That’ll show you what bad string is crashing your app.

            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 className="text-sm font-semibold text-red-400 mb-1">WEAKNESSES</h3>
              <ul className="text-sm space-y-1">
                {weaknesses.map((item, i) => (
                  <li key={i} className="flex justify-between">
                    <span>{item}</span>
                    <span className="text-yellow-400 font-bold">⚠</span>
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <button className="bg-blue-600 text-white py-2 rounded mt-6 text-sm font-semibold shadow hover:bg-blue-700">
          Unlock full report
        </button>
      </div>

      {/* Main Content */}
      <div className="flex-1 p-8 space-y-6">
        <h1 className="text-xl font-bold text-green-600">
          {status === "loading"
            ? "Loading..."
            : `Hi, ${session?.user?.name || session?.user?.email || "User"}`}
        </h1>

        <div
          className={`p-6 rounded shadow space-y-4 ${
            theme === "dark" ? "bg-gray-900 text-white" : "bg-white"
          }`}
        >
          <h2 className="text-lg font-bold">
            Your resume scored {score !== null ? `${score} out of 100` : "is loading..."}
          </h2>

          {feedback && (
            <p
              className={`text-sm italic border-l-4 pl-4 ${
                theme === "dark"
                  ? "text-yellow-200 border-yellow-600"
                  : "text-gray-700 border-yellow-400"
              }`}
            >
              {feedback}
            </p>
          )}

          <div className="w-full h-4 bg-gradient-to-r from-red-400 via-yellow-300 to-green-400 rounded mt-3 relative">
            <div
              className="absolute top-0 h-4 bg-purple-600 rounded"
              style={{ width: `${score ?? 0}%` }}
            ></div>
          </div>

          <div className="mt-4">
            <h3 className="text-sm font-semibold">Suggestions</h3>
            <ul className="text-sm mt-2 space-y-1">
              {suggestions.map((item, i) => (
                <li
                  key={i}
                  className={`list-disc list-inside ${
                    theme === "dark" ? "text-gray-300" : "text-gray-700"
                  }`}
                >
                  {item}
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div
            className={`flex items-start border rounded p-3 mt-4 text-sm ${
              theme === "dark"
                ? "bg-yellow-950 border-yellow-600 text-yellow-300"
                : "bg-yellow-50 border-yellow-300 text-yellow-800"
            }`}
          >
            <AlertTriangle size={16} className="mr-2 mt-0.5" />
            Use this feedback to revise your resume and try again.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* Resume Preview */}
      <div className="w-[600px] border-l p-4 overflow-auto">
        <h2 className="text-sm font-semibold mb-2">Resume Preview</h2>
        {previewURL ? (
          <iframe
            src={previewURL}
            className="w-full h-[90vh] border"
            title="Resume Preview"
          />
        ) : (
          <p className="text-sm italic text-gray-400">No resume uploaded.</p>
        )}
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}

    js
    app.use(cors({
  origin: "http://localhost:3000",
  credentials: true
}));

  • 401 error: Ensure you're saving access_token correctly after login, and it's valid for the /resume/scores POST.

python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from matplotlib.patches import Rectangle

# Sample color palette from your boss (just guessing from code)
colors = {
    "lavender_bg": "#F4EEFF",
    "purple": "#845EC2",
    "light_section": "#FAFAFF",
    "cta_red": "#FF6F61",
    "card_border": "#B3E5FC",
    "dark_text": "#2D2D2D",
    "gray_text": "#666666",
    "white": "white",
}

# Set up the figure
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 10))
ax.axis('off')
fig.patch.set_facecolor(colors["lavender_bg"])  # Background

# Header
ax.add_patch(Rectangle((0.05, 0.9), 0.9, 0.07, color=colors["purple"]))
ax.text(0.5, 0.935, "🚀 Boost My Resume", ha='center', va='center',
        fontsize=16, weight='bold', color=colors["white"])

# Hero Section
ax.add_patch(Rectangle((0.05, 0.75), 0.9, 0.1, facecolor=colors["light_section"]))
ax.text(0.5, 0.81, "Land Your Dream Job with AI", ha='center', va='center',
        fontsize=14, weight='bold', color=colors["dark_text"])
ax.text(0.5, 0.78, "Smart resume tips. Real-world insights. Gen-AI powered.",
        ha='center', va='center', fontsize=10, color=colors["gray_text"])

# CTA Button
ax.add_patch(Rectangle((0.3, 0.7), 0.4, 0.05, facecolor=colors["cta_red"]))
ax.text(0.5, 0.725, "Upload Resume", ha='center', va='center',
        fontsize=10, weight='bold', color=colors["white"])

# Feature Cards
features = [
    "✅ Personalized Resume Feedback",
    "✅ Interview Prep Tips & Frameworks",
    "✅ Gen-AI Trends in Career Growth"
]

for i, text in enumerate(features):
    y = 0.64 - i * 0.07
    ax.add_patch(Rectangle((0.08, y), 0.84, 0.06,
                  facecolor=colors["light_section"], edgecolor=colors["card_border"]))
    ax.text(0.1, y + 0.03, text, ha='left', va='center',
            fontsize=9, color=colors["dark_text"])

# Footer
ax.add_patch(Rectangle((0, 0.05), 1, 0.05, facecolor=colors["purple"]))
ax.text(0.5, 0.075, "© 2025 BoostMyResume | All rights reserved",
        ha='center', va='center', fontsize=8, color=colors["white"])

# Show layout
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

💡 What is a Mockup?

A mockup is a visual draft or representation of how a product (like a website, app, or feature) will look. It's not functional, but it shows the design layout, colors, fonts, and visual elements.

🖼️ Example in Your Case:

You used Matplotlib to draw a landing page layout — that’s a mockup.

It shows:

  • A purple header with the app name ✅

  • A hero section with tagline and subtext ✅

  • A big CTA button (“Upload Resume”) ✅

  • Feature blocks ✅

  • Footer ✅

All of this is static, meant to communicate design before coding the real frontend.

🔧 Why Use a Mockup?

PurposeExample
✅ Show layout before coding“Where should the CTA go?”
✅ Share with boss/team“Do these colors work?”
✅ Plan mobile or desktop UI“Will this fit on phones?”

TermMeaning

PrototypeA clickable or interactive version (using Figma, etc.)
